01/10/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A fire broke out at the St Jovan Bigorski Monastery, near Debar, early Wednesday (September 30th) causing major property damage but no injuries. 
Fire crews from several cities, backed by helicopters, work to extinguish the blaze. 
The church that is part of the monastery complex was not affected, and monks managed to save the most valuable icons. 
An investigation is under way. 
Damage is estimated at 5.5m euros. 
(A1, Makfax, MRT, MIA - 30/09/09)
